"use strict";(self.webpackChunkjosp_docs=self.webpackChunkjosp_docs||[]).push([[1477],{30010:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"public-jcp-updated","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/public-jcp-updated","source":"@site/blog/2021-10-05-Public-JCP-updated.mdx","title":"Public JCP updated to v2.2.1","description":"Public John Cloud Platform updated to latest JCP version 2.2.1","date":"2021-10-05T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"October 5, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.065,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Public JCP updated to v2.2.1","description":"Public John Cloud Platform updated to latest JCP version 2.2.1","slug":"public-jcp-updated","authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}]},"nextItem":{"title":"Released JOD Dist TMPL v1.0.1","permalink":"/blog/released-joddisttmpl-1.0.1"}},"content":"Tonight we updated the Public JCP instances to latest JOSP version 2.2.1.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e"},{"id":"released-joddisttmpl-1.0.1","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/released-joddisttmpl-1.0.1","source":"@site/blog/2021-10-02-Released-JOD-Dist-TMPL-1.0.1.mdx","title":"Released JOD Dist TMPL v1.0.1","description":"Released JOD Distribution TEMPLATE version 1.0.1","date":"2021-10-02T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"October 2, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.305,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Released JOD Dist TMPL v1.0.1","description":"Released JOD Distribution TEMPLATE version 1.0.1","slug":"released-joddisttmpl-1.0.1","authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}]},"prevItem":{"title":"Public JCP updated to v2.2.1","permalink":"/blog/public-jcp-updated"},"nextItem":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.2.1","permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.2.1"}},"content":"Updated JOD Distribution TEMPLATE to version 1.0.1.\\n\\nAmong other things, the most important changes were:\\n\\n* Set 2.2.1 as default JOD Version\\n* Added full support for Windows via powershell\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nCheck out the [JOD Dist TMPL] documentation for more info and full list of his features. Or visit related guides:\\n\\n* [Create new JOD Distribution](/references/tools/jod_dist_template/create_your_own_jod_distribution/start_new_jod_distribution)\\n* [Run a JOD Distribution](/references/tools/jod_dist_template/how_to_use_a_jod_distribution/get_a_jod_distribution)"},{"id":"released-josp-2.2.1","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.2.1","source":"@site/blog/2021-10-01-Released-JOSP-2.2.1.mdx","title":"Released JOSP v2.2.1","description":"Released JOSP project version 2.2.1","date":"2021-10-01T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"October 1, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.22,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.2.1","description":"Released JOSP project version 2.2.1","slug":"released-josp-2.2.1","authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}]},"prevItem":{"title":"Released JOD Dist TMPL v1.0.1","permalink":"/blog/released-joddisttmpl-1.0.1"},"nextItem":{"title":"Released JOD Dist TMPL v1.0","permalink":"/blog/released-joddisttmpl-1.0"}},"content":"Today we released the **John OS Platform version 2.2.1** with bug fixes from version 2.2.0.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n:::info\\n**John O.S. Platform v 2.2.1**\\n\\n* [Source code](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.2.1/)\\n* [Project docs](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.2.1/docs/INDEX.md)\\n* [Published Libraries](https://search.maven.org/search?q=com.robypomper.josp)\\n  :::\\n\\nTo start experiment with your own IoT Eco-System see the [JOSP Docs](/)."},{"id":"released-joddisttmpl-1.0","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/released-joddisttmpl-1.0","source":"@site/blog/2021-09-19-Released-JOD-Dist-TMPL-1.0.mdx","title":"Released JOD Dist TMPL v1.0","description":"Released JOD Distribution TEMPLATE version 1.0","date":"2021-09-19T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 19, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.62,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Released JOD Dist TMPL v1.0","description":"Released JOD Distribution TEMPLATE version 1.0","slug":"released-joddisttmpl-1.0","authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}]},"prevItem":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.2.1","permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.2.1"},"nextItem":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.2.0","permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.2.0"}},"content":"With this tool, you can **create a JOD Distribution in minutes**.\\n\\nA JOD Distribution is a compressed archive that can be shared among user and allow them integrates JOSP Objects to their IoT EcoSystem. Users can download and install a [JOD Distribution](/references/jod_dists/) on their computer, on remote devices or whatever the JOD Distribution require (it\'s common for a JOD Distribution to be hardware dependant). Once installed and running, the JOD Distribution expose a JOSP Objects to the [Public JCP](https://www.johnosproject.org/frontend/index.html).\\n\\nWith the JOD Distribution TEMPLATE, anyone can create his own JOD Distribution in minutes.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nCheck out the [JOD Dist TMPL] documentation for more info and full list of his features. Or visit related guides:\\n\\n* [Create new JOD Distribution](/references/tools/jod_dist_template/create_your_own_jod_distribution/start_new_jod_distribution)\\n* [Run a JOD Distribution](/references/tools/jod_dist_template/how_to_use_a_jod_distribution/get_a_jod_distribution)"},{"id":"released-josp-2.2.0","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.2.0","source":"@site/blog/2021-08-02-Released-JOSP-2.2.0.mdx","title":"Released JOSP v2.2.0","description":"Released JOSP project version 2.2.0","date":"2021-08-02T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 2, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":1.065,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.2.0","description":"Released JOSP project version 2.2.0","slug":"released-josp-2.2.0","authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}]},"prevItem":{"title":"Released JOD Dist TMPL v1.0","permalink":"/blog/released-joddisttmpl-1.0"},"nextItem":{"title":"Opened the official YouTube channel","permalink":"/blog/opened-official-youtube-channel"}},"content":"I\'m happy to announce the **John OS Platform version 2.2.0** with the new JCP microservices *JCP Front End* and *JCP JSL Web Bridge*.\\n\\nThis release solves many bugs encountered during version 2.1.0 development and increase communication stability.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n:::info\\n**John O.S. Platform v 2.2.0**\\n\\n* [Source code](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.2.0/)\\n* [Project docs](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.2.0/docs/INDEX.md)\\n* [Published Libraries](https://search.maven.org/search?q=com.robypomper.josp)\\n  :::\\n\\nThe John OS Platform project provide a suit of software and tools to simplify the IoT solutions design. From his source code\'s ```README.md``` file:\\n\\n:::note The John O.S. Project (JOSP for friends) simplify the design and build process of modern [Internet of Things solutions](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.0.0/docs/josp_ecosystems.md):\\n\\n* reduces **smart object\'s creation a 5 minutes activity**, even without coding skills\\n* it\'s possible integrate any kind of connected object, regardless of communication protocol used by the object\\n* develop custom **software that easily interact with objects**\\n* startups local and cloud connections between service and objects out-of-the-box\\n* it provides communication **security and object\'s access control by design**\\n* it\'s completely Open Source\\n  :::\\n\\nThis version introduces all 2 micro-services for the John Cloud Platform component:\\n\\n* [JOSP JSL Web Bridge](/references/josp/jcp/microservices/jslwb/): the JSL\'s HTTP APIs manager for JSL services as web clients\\n* [JOSP Front End](/references/josp/jcp/microservices/fe/): the JCP front end\\n\\nTo start experiment with your own IoT Eco-System see the [JOSP Docs](/)."},{"id":"opened-official-youtube-channel","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/opened-official-youtube-channel","source":"@site/blog/2021-06-11-Opened-official-YouTube-channel.mdx","title":"Opened the official YouTube channel","description":"Now it available the official JOSP project YouTube channel","date":"2021-06-11T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 11, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.19,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Opened the official YouTube channel","description":"Now it available the official JOSP project YouTube channel","slug":"opened-official-youtube-channel","authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}]},"prevItem":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.2.0","permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.2.0"},"nextItem":{"title":"Public JCP Startup","permalink":"/blog/public-jcp-startup"}},"content":"Created the **new [John O.S. Project @ YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCb4HveVMSmCaSaluou6D3xQ) channel**.\\n\\nHere we will post all JOSP\'s videos like guides, tutorials and videos how-tos. [Subscribe](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCb4HveVMSmCaSaluou6D3xQ?sub_confirmation=1) to this channel or check this blog, to keep updated on new video release.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e"},{"id":"public-jcp-startup","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/public-jcp-startup","source":"@site/blog/2021-02-05-Public-JCP-Startup.mdx","title":"Public JCP Startup","description":"Now the Public John Cloud Platform is available","date":"2021-02-05T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"February 5, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.515,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Public JCP Startup","description":"Now the Public John Cloud Platform is available","slug":"public-jcp-startup","authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}]},"prevItem":{"title":"Opened the official YouTube channel","permalink":"/blog/opened-official-youtube-channel"},"nextItem":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.1.0","permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.1.0"}},"content":"Today **we launched the public John Cloud Platform instances**.\\n\\nFrom today, you can go to [www.johnosproject.org/frontend](https://www.johnosproject.org/frontend) and access to your IoT EcoSystem. Let\'s start connect objects and interact with them directly from the web or one of the [JOSP Services](/references/jsl_services/).\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nThe new JCP Front End is now available as the entire John Cloud Platform at [johnosproject.org](https://www.johnosproject.org). Now you can connect your JOSP Objects and Services to this Public JCP instance and enable the cloud communication troughs objects and services.\\n\\nLet\'s go to the new JCP Front End and register yourself, then looks for [JOD Distributions list](/references/jod_dists/) for a list of connectable objects."},{"id":"released-josp-2.1.0","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.1.0","source":"@site/blog/2021-02-01-Released-JOSP-2.1.0.mdx","title":"Released JOSP v2.1.0","description":"Released JOSP project version 2.1.0","date":"2021-02-01T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"February 1, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.4,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.1.0","description":"Released JOSP project version 2.1.0","slug":"released-josp-2.1.0","authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}]},"prevItem":{"title":"Public JCP Startup","permalink":"/blog/public-jcp-startup"},"nextItem":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.0.0","permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.0.0"}},"content":"Here the release **John OS Platform version 2.1.0** (not released).\\n\\nThis version did not approve the release process. So it\'s only an internal version. It includes updates for the JOD Agent, the JSL library and the JCP platform components JCP APIs and JCP GWs. It includes also a partial implementation of the JCP FE and JCP JSL WB microservice of the JCP platform.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n:::info\\n**John O.S. Platform v 2.0.0**\\n\\n* Source code\\n* Project docs\\n* Published Libraries\\n  :::"},{"id":"released-josp-2.0.0","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.0.0","source":"@site/blog/2020-08-04-Released-JOSP-2.0.0.mdx","title":"Released JOSP v2.0.0","description":"Released JOSP project version 2.0.0","date":"2020-08-04T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 4, 2020","tags":[],"readingTime":1.51,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.0.0","description":"Released JOSP project version 2.0.0","slug":"released-josp-2.0.0","authors":[{"name":"Roberto Pompermaier"}]},"prevItem":{"title":"Released JOSP v2.1.0","permalink":"/blog/released-josp-2.1.0"}},"content":"I\'m happy to announce the **John OS Platform version 2.0.0**.\\n\\nWe published the first release of the 2.x.x series.<br/>\\nIt includes the JOD Agent, the JSL library and a minimal implementation of the JCP platform (JCP APIs and JCP GWs).<br/>\\nWith this version you can startup a JOSP EcoSystem with multiple JOSP Objects and Services that can communicate directly or via JCP.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n:::info\\n**John O.S. Platform v 2.0.0**\\n\\n* [Source code](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.0.0/)\\n* [Project docs](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.0.0/docs/INDEX.md)\\n* [Published Libraries](https://search.maven.org/search?q=com.robypomper.josp)\\n  :::\\n\\nThe John OS Platform project provide a suit of software and tools to simplify the IoT solutions design. From his source code\'s ```README.md``` file:\\n\\n:::note The John O.S. Project (JOSP for friends) simplify the design and build process of modern [Internet of Things solutions](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.0.0/docs/josp_ecosystems.md):\\n\\n* reduces **smart object\'s creation a 5 minutes activity**, even without coding skills\\n* it\'s possible integrate any kind of connected object, regardless of communication protocol used by the object\\n* develop custom **software that easily interact with objects**\\n* startups local and cloud connections between service and objects out-of-the-box\\n* it provides communication **security and object\'s access control by design**\\n* it\'s completely Open Source\\n  :::\\n\\nThis version introduces all 3 main components for a JOSP EcoSystem.\\n\\n* The **Object\'s agent [JOSP JOD](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.0.0/docs/jospJOD/README.md)** can be installed on a smart object and allow to expose all object\'s status and actions to services like the environment temperature or ths light status.\\n* Services are **all software that include the [JOSP JSL](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.0.0/docs/jospJSL/README.md) library**. This library allows software easily interact with JOD objects:\\n  1. listing and filter available objects,\\n  1. getting status updates and\\n  1. send action commands.\\n* The **cloud components [JCP APIs](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.0.0/docs/jcpAPIs/README.md) and the [JOSP GWs](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.0.0/docs/jospGWs/README.md)** components allow objects and services to communicate also remotely via Cloud.\\n\\nTo start experiment with your own IoT Eco-System see the [JOSP Project documentation](https://bitbucket.org/johnosproject_shared/com.robypomper.josp/src/2.0.0/docs/INDEX.md)."}]}')}}]);